              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Peak energy of Maxwellian normal energy distribution",
                " is 26 milli-eV, the energy of the most probable flux",
                " in the wavelength representation of the Maxwellian",
                " flux is 75.5 milli-eV.",
                "The neutron spectrum is approximated by a Maxwellian",
                " distribution of temperature 350 deg-K."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "6.E+10 to 3.E+11 atoms deposited on 9.5-mm diameter",
                " platinum disk. Samples obtained by chemical separation",
                " of uranium grown in a 15-min period by alpha decay",
                " of plutonium solution (200-400 mg Pu)."
              ]
            }
          ],
